I love getting little updates about how you guys are doing. It's really cool to see Flynn develop from the newborn baby we got to see to this happy human :)
Edit: I forgot to say that I love the fact that you guys are incorporating some sign language in Flynn's life. I don't know how accurate it is but a friend of mine told me when she had a baby that babies are able to learn signs before they are able to talk, and it seems really smart to me to give your child as many ways to communicate as possible :) And I imagine it's extra fun given your brother Trent and the fact that sign language used to be a big part of your life at one point, before the cochlear implant.
